entry.title: The Commission for Healthcare Audit and Inspection (Membership) Regulations 2003

ukm:Subject.Value: NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICE, ENGLAND AND WALES

category.term: NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICE, ENGLAND AND WALES

entry.summary: These Regulations make provision concerning membership of the Commission for Healthcare Audit and Inspection (the CHAI) established by section 41(1) of the Health and Social Care (Community Health and Standards) Act 2003. In particular, they make provision for the numbers and tenure of office of members (regulations 2 and 3), disqualification for appointment or from holding office (regulations 4 and 5), for suspension from office (regulation 6) and for termination of the tenure of office of a member (regulation 7).

entry.title: The Producer Responsibility Obligations (Packaging Waste) (Amendment) (England) Regulations 2003

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Producer Responsibility Obligations (Packaging Waste) (Amendment) (England) Regulations 2003

entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Producer Responsibility Obligations (Packaging Waste) Regulations 1997 (the “1997 Regulations”), which imposed on producers, and, on their behalf, operators of schemes, obligations to recover and recycle specified tonnages of packaging waste, and related obligations, in order to attain the targets in Article 6(1) of Directive 94/62/EC ( the “Directive”) which had to be met in 2001. A revision of the Directive which will set new targets to be met in 2008 is presently being negotiated and is expected to be agreed by the end of 2003. In order to ensure that the absence of targets higher than those presently in the 1997 Regulations does not prejudice the United Kingdom`s ability to increase its rates of recovery and recycling sufficiently to meet the new Directive targets in 2008, these Regulations set interim domestic targets and recovery and recycling obligations which take account of the probable new targets which the United Kingdom is likely to have to meet in 2008.

entry.title: The Welfare of Animals (Slaughter or Killing) (Amendment) (England) Regulations 2003
entry.summary: These Regulations, which apply to England only, amend the Welfare of Animals (Slaughter or Killing) Regulations 1995 (“the 1995 Regulations”). The 1995 Regulations give effect to Council Directive 93/119/EC on the protection of animals at the time of slaughter or killing (OJ No. L 340, 31.12.93, p.21). These Regulations amend Schedules 1, 4, 6 and 9 to the 1995 Regulations.

entry.title: The Environmental Protection (Controls on Dangerous Substances) Regulations 2003
entry.summary: These Regulations give effect to European Parliament and Council Directive 2002/45/EC which amended for the twentieth time Council Directive 76/769/EEC on the approximation of the laws, regulations and administrative provisions of the Member States relating to restrictions on the marketing and use of certain dangerous substances and preparations. They also give effect to European Commission Directive 2003/2/EC relating to restrictions on the marketing and use of arsenic (tenth adaptation to technical progress to Council Directive 76/769/EEC). They revoke the Environmental Protection (Controls on Hexachloroethane) Regulations 2003, S.I. 2003/602 and re-enact the prohibition contained in those Regulations. These Regulations extend to Great Britain.

title.div: The African Swine Fever (Wales) Order 2003 / Gorchymyn Clwy Affricanaidd y Moch (Cymru) 2003

div.p: This Order, which applies to Wales, implements Council Directive 2002/60/EC (OJ No. L192, 20.07.2002, p.27) revising Community measures for the control of African swine fever. It revokes and replaces the African Swine Fever Order 1980 so far as it applies to Wales.

entry.title: Street Works (Recovery of Costs) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2003
entry.summary: These Regulations prescribe the basis for calculating the costs or expenses which an authority, body or person may recover under the provisions of the Street Works (Northern Ireland) Order 1995 (“the Order”).

entry.title: The Public Appointments and Public Bodies etc. (Scotland) Act 2003 (Commencement No. 4) Order 2003
entry.summary: The Order brings into force sections 5 to 10 and 17 of, and paragraphs 4 (partially) and 5(15) of Schedule 4 to the Public Appointments and Public Bodies etc. (Scotland) Act 2003 (“the Act”), relating to health service bodies.

entry.title: Infant Formula and Follow-on Formula (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2003
entry.summary: These Regulations, which amend the Infant Formula and Follow-on Formula Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1995, as amended, implement Commission Directive 2003/14/EC amending Directive 91/321/EEC on infant formulae and follow-on formulae.

entry.title: The Extradition Act 2003 (Commencement and Savings) (Amendment) Order 2003
entry.summary: This Order amends the Extradition Act 2003 (Commencement and Savings) Order 2003 by replacing article 5 of that Order. Under article 5, as substituted, the Extradition Act 1989 continues to have effect in the Crown dependencies and British overseas territories (with the exception of Gibraltar) until the coming into force of provisions which replace that Act in the dependency or territory in question. The provision might be passed by the legislature of the dependency or territory or be included in an Order in Council under sections 177 and 178 of the Extradition Act 2003 in the case of a territory or an Order in Council under section 222 of that Act in the case of a dependency.

entry.title: Act of Sederunt (Taking of Evidence in the European Community) 2003
entry.summary: This Act of Sederunt makes rules of procedure in the sheriff court for applications for requests to take evidence in the Member States of the European Community.

entry.title: Designation of Schools Having a Religious Character (Independent Schools) (England) (No.2) Order 2003
entry.summary: This Order designates the independent schools named herein as having a religious character.

entry.title: The Financing of Maintained Schools (England) (No. 2) Regulations 2003
entry.summary: A local education authority’s individual schools budget is to be divided between the schools which they maintain in the form of budget shares for each school. These Regulations provide the basis on which, for the financial year beginning on 1st April 2004, a local education authority may determine the amount from their individual schools budget to be allocated to each school as its budget share for that financial year.

entry.title: The Criminal Justice (No. 2) (Northern Ireland) Order 2003 (repealed)
entry.summary: This Order is made only for purposes corresponding to the purposes of section 3(3) of the Criminal Justice Act 2003. Its effect is that possession of cannabis shall continue to be an arrestable offence irrespective of the maximum period of imprisonment for conviction of that offence.

entry.title: The Food Benefit Schemes (Northern Ireland) Order 2003
entry.summary: This Order is made only for purposes corresponding to those of section 185 of the Health and Social Care (Community Health and Standards) Act 2003. The Order provides for the replacement of welfare food schemes under Article 13 of the Social Security (Northern Ireland) Order 1988.
